# Feature Delivery Contract

When asked to implement a feature, ship it end-to-end and consistent with existing modules.

## Do
- First inspect at least one similar existing feature and mirror its structure and naming.
- Implement all required layers: UI (Compose), ViewModel/state, domain/use-case, repository/service wiring.
- Keep unidirectional data flow and ViewModel-driven state.
- Use Hilt dependency injection patterns already present in the codebase.
- Integrate analytics/navigation/remote-config only through existing core module APIs.
- Run all unit tests before finalizing. Do not run Android tests.

## Do not
- Invent new architectural layers, generic "utility" abstractions, or ad-hoc base classes.
- Place business logic in composables or framework plumbing in domain code.
- Leave TODO placeholders for required behavior unless explicitly requested.
